<p><b>Can you put foil in a combi microwave?</b> Some microwaves are combo units, Microwave/Convection Oven/Air Fryer. In these types of microwaves, it is safe to use aluminum foil when using any function that is not the microwave. Any other type of Microwave, the foil would start to spark.</p>
<p><b>Can you put metal in a combi microwave?</b> Metal cookware should not be used in a microwave. Metal will not allow microwaves to penetrate the food so any food behind the metal will not be cooked. The metal could also cause arcing in the oven. Metal and foil can be used safely and effectively with the convection cooking feature in a microwave convection oven.</p>
